Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}, turn halfway through cooking. Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}), leave to the side.

Zest the @lemon{1/2} then cut into wedges. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%sprig}(finely chopped) (stalks and all) and put half of it into a #bowl{} with the lemon zest. Add the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside - this is for the fish. Finely chop the @capers{15%g} and put into another bowl with three quarters of the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, the remaining parsley and a squeeze of lemon juice. Mix together and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. This is your tartare sauce.

Lay the @sea bass fillets{2} skin-side down on a baking tray lined with #baking paper{}. Divide the remaining mayonnaise between the fish and spread over evenly, covering the top. Spoon the breadcrumb mixture on top of the mayonnaise on the fish. Press it down with a #spoon{} and drizzle with @olive oil{}. When the wedges are about halfway through cooking, bake the fish on the middle shelf of the oven until the crumbs are golden and the fish is cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Squeeze half the lemon juice into a bowl and add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together. Halve the @premium tomato mix{125%g} and pop them into the bowl with the dressing, toss together and set aside.

7 mins before the fish is cooked, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the @sugar snap peas{150%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until slightly charred and tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic and stir-fry together with the sugar snaps for ~{1%minute}. Remove the pan from the heat.

When everything is ready add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the tomatoes and toss together. Season the wedges with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Serve the fish with the wedges and sugar snaps alongside with a dollop of tartare sauce and a lemon wedge. Serve with your bowl of salad alongside and enjoy!